            But there was a little competition with the sea here: who can make it across the rocks with dry feet? On the way there I lost. On the way back I didn't even try anymore and simply walked barefoot through the water.
        </p>
        <p>
            At the restaurant or rather café up at the parking lot we treated ourselves to an ice cream and something to drink afterwards, before the next highlight awaited us – as it would turn out later.
        </p>
        <p>
            Marina di Ragusa!
            <br />
            The place excited us just as much as Cefalù. No, not in the same way actually. Simply differently. Because here there was what we had been missing a little until then: a wonderful, wide sandy beach with gloriously soft sand. Exactly how we had imagined Sicily.
        </p>
        <p>
            We spent the entire afternoon at the beach, enjoyed the sun and simply let our souls dangle.
        </p>

